entry.def: The stub of a cigarette or a pencil is the last short piece of it which remains when the rest has been used.

example.ex: He pulled the stub of a pencil from behind his ear.
example.tran: 他从耳后拿出一小段铅笔头。

entry.def: A ticket stub is the part that you keep when you go in to watch a performance.

example.ex: Fans who still have their original ticket stubs should contact Sheffield Arena by July 3.
example.tran: 仍保留原始票根的球迷请于 7 月 3 号前和谢菲尔德体育馆联系。

entry.def: A cheque stub is the small part that you keep as a record of what you have paid.
If you stub your toe, you hurt it by accidentally kicking something.

example.ex: I stubbed my toes against a table leg.
example.tran: 我不小心踢到桌子腿上。

means.word_mean: 1. a short piece remaining on a trunk or stem where a branch is lost
3. a torn part of a ticket returned to the holder as a receipt
4. the part of a check that is retained as a record
5. the small unused part of something (especially the end of a cigarette that is left after smoking)
